                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Truman–Attlee talks were discussed by the National Security Council at its
                    74th meeting on December 11, and at the request of President Truman the
                    Department of State prepared a report for the Council recording the results of
                    the talks. This report, designated <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 93 and
                    dated December 12, not printed, incorporated the substance of the Final
                    Communiqué and the agreements and disagreements that emerged on various policy
                    questions during the course of the conversations. Documentation relating to
                    these developments, <pb facs="1813" n="1789" xml:id="pg_1789"/> including the
                    text of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 93, is in the Executive Secretariat
                    Files.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
